fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.design

Interface IPageAsset

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAttachable

    @PluginService
public interface IPageAsset
extends IAttachable
    Provides a reference to other resources that may be attached to a page, such as stylesheets or scripts. Such assets may be standalone or belong to groups of related resources.

    In the case of stylesheets, a page asset can represent a stylesheet that is not a member of any specific template package. In the same way, template packages should generally not expose the stylesheets they contain using this interface.

    To make an implementation available, register it as an OSGi service. For assets in indissociable groups, only the main asset of the group needs to be registered.

    Thread safety: implementations are expected to be immutable and completely thread-safe.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

      • REL_BOOKMARK

        static final String REL_BOOKMARK
        Refers to a bookmark. A bookmark is a link to a key entry point within an extended document. The title attribute may be used, for example, to label the bookmark. Note that several bookmarks may be defined in each document.
        Since:

        See Also:
        getRelation(), Constant Field Values

      • REL_PREFETCH

        static final String REL_PREFETCH
        Extension that refers to a link to be prefetched (when the user agent is idle) before the user selects a link (in anticipation).

        This link relation type should only be used where there is a strong possibility that the referenced asset will actually be required, as excessive usage will require additional network and server capacity.

        More information can be found on the Mozilla Developer Network.

        Note: the Google Chrome user agent uses the link type "prerender" instead of "prefetch".

        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        getRelation(), Constant Field Values

      • getAddress

        String getAddress()
        Gets the path mapping for this asset. The actual resource is not provided via this interface: this simply indicates that a page can include a reference to a resource provided by an addressable service or by some other HTTP server.

        An absolute address is a complete URL (note: care should be taken when mixing HTTP and HTTPS protocols, as some browsers may refuse to load any HTTP resources when HTTPS is being used). A relative address is a URI relative to the base path of the HTTP service.

        Unlike an IAddressableService, wildcard patterns are not allowed. When the asset belongs to a group, the asset should provide a reference to the group.

        Returns:
        a string, starting with "/" (relative to the base path) and ending the path with either "/" or the name of the asset.
        Since:
        1.0

      • getRelation

        String getRelation()
        Gets the list of relation type keywords.

        This can for example return "alternate stylesheet".

        More information can be found in the W3 specification.

        Returns:
        the relation type keywords, as a space-separated string, or an empty string (never null).
        Since:
        1.0
